-- English Advanced
('Technology has revolutionized the way we communicate and interact with each other in modern society. From smartphones to social media platforms, digital innovation continues to shape our daily lives in unprecedented ways. The internet connects billions of people across the globe, enabling instant communication and information sharing. Cloud computing allows us to access our data from anywhere, while artificial intelligence assists us in making better decisions. However, these advancements also bring challenges such as privacy concerns, digital addiction, and the spread of misinformation. As we embrace new technologies, it is crucial to maintain a balance between innovation and responsibility. Education systems must adapt to prepare students for a digital future, teaching not only technical skills but also critical thinking and digital literacy.', 'english', 'advanced', 'medium', 'ready', 'manual', 125),

('Climate change represents one of the most pressing challenges facing humanity today. Rising global temperatures are causing ice caps to melt, sea levels to rise, and weather patterns to become increasingly unpredictable. Scientists warn that without immediate action to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, the consequences could be catastrophic. Renewable energy sources such as solar, wind, and hydroelectric power offer promising alternatives to fossil fuels. Governments worldwide are implementing policies to encourage sustainable practices and reduce carbon footprints. Individuals can also make a difference by adopting eco-friendly habits like recycling, using public transportation, and reducing energy consumption. The transition to a sustainable future requires collective effort from governments, businesses, and citizens. By working together and making conscious choices, we can protect our planet for future generations.', 'english', 'advanced', 'medium', 'ready', 'manual', 130),

('The human brain is one of the most complex and fascinating organs in the body. It contains approximately eighty-six billion neurons that communicate through electrical and chemical signals. These neurons form intricate networks that enable us to think, feel, remember, and make decisions. Neuroscience research has revealed that the brain is remarkably plastic, meaning it can reorganize itself by forming new neural connections throughout life. This neuroplasticity allows us to learn new skills, adapt to changing environments, and recover from injuries. Memory formation involves multiple brain regions working together to encode, store, and retrieve information. Understanding how the brain works has important implications for treating neurological disorders, improving education, and enhancing cognitive performance. As technology advances, brain imaging techniques provide deeper insights into the mysteries of human consciousness and cognition.', 'english', 'advanced', 'medium', 'ready', 'manual', 140),

('Space exploration has captured human imagination for centuries, driving scientific discovery and technological innovation. The launch of Sputnik in nineteen fifty-seven marked the beginning of the space age, followed by the historic moon landing in nineteen sixty-nine. Today, space agencies and private companies are working together to push the boundaries of what is possible. Mars missions aim to search for signs of past or present life on the red planet. The International Space Station serves as a laboratory for conducting experiments in microgravity. Satellite technology has transformed communication, navigation, and weather forecasting on Earth. Looking ahead, ambitious projects include establishing permanent lunar bases and sending humans to Mars. These endeavors not only expand our knowledge of the universe but also inspire future generations to pursue careers in science and engineering.', 'english', 'advanced', 'medium', 'ready', 'manual', 145),

('Artificial intelligence is transforming industries and reshaping the future of work. Machine learning algorithms can analyze vast amounts of data to identify patterns and make predictions with remarkable accuracy. AI applications range from virtual assistants and recommendation systems to autonomous vehicles and medical diagnosis. In healthcare, AI helps doctors detect diseases earlier and develop personalized treatment plans. In finance, algorithms detect fraudulent transactions and optimize investment strategies. Manufacturing benefits from AI-powered robots that increase efficiency and precision. However, the rise of AI also raises important questions about job displacement, algorithmic bias, and ethical considerations. As AI systems become more sophisticated, society must ensure they are developed and deployed responsibly. Education and training programs need to prepare workers for an AI-driven economy while addressing concerns about privacy and security.', 'english', 'advanced', 'medium', 'ready', 'manual', 142),

-- Lao Advanced
('ເຕັກໂນໂລຊີໄດ້ປ່ຽນແປງວິທີທີ່ພວກເຮົາສື່ສານແລະພົວພັນກັນໃນສັງຄົມທີ່ທັນສະໄໝ. ຈາກໂທລະສັບສະຫຼາດໄປຫາເວທີສື່ສັງຄົມອອນໄລນ໌, ນະວັດຕະກຳດິຈິຕອນຍັງສືບຕໍ່ສ້າງຮູບແບບຊີວິດປະຈຳວັນຂອງພວກເຮົາໃນທາງທີ່ບໍ່ເຄີຍມີມາກ່ອນ. ອິນເຕີເນັດເຊື່ອມຕໍ່ຜູ້ຄົນຫຼາຍພັນລ້ານຄົນທົ່ວໂລກ, ເຮັດໃຫ້ການສື່ສານແລະການແບ່ງປັນຂໍ້ມູນເປັນໄປໄດ້ທັນທີ. ການຄຳນວນແບບຄລາວອະນຸຍາດໃຫ້ພວກເຮົາເຂົ້າເຖິງຂໍ້ມູນຂອງພວກເຮົາຈາກທຸກບ່ອນ, ໃນຂະນະທີ່ປັນຍາປະດິດຊ່ວຍພວກເຮົາໃນການຕັດສິນໃຈທີ່ດີກວ່າ. ຢ່າງໃດກໍຕາມ, ຄວາມກ້າວໜ້າເຫຼົ່ານີ້ຍັງນຳມາເຊິ່ງສິ່ງທ້າທາຍເຊັ່ນ: ຄວາມກັງວົນກ່ຽວກັບຄວາມເປັນສ່ວນຕົວ, ການຕິດດິຈິຕອນ, ແລະການແຜ່ກະຈາຍຂໍ້ມູນທີ່ບໍ່ຖືກຕ້ອງ.', 'lao', 'advanced', 'medium', 'ready', 'manual', 110);

